====================================================================
 WHY IT FAILS — THE CORE PROBLEM
====================================================================
 The opponent's spell burst (1152 raw) vs your attack DPS:

   With Res=10: survive burst only if MaxBody > 652 (need Str=23+)
                => impossible, minimum 13 Str primaries not available.

   With Res=16: burst = 969. Survive if MaxBody > 469.
                Survivable! But kill time = 160s. They regen 2 spells
                before you kill them. Those 2 regens + attacks kill you.

   The real constraint: killing 1000hp in time is fighting THEIR
   defensive Mind layer + their offensive spell bursts simultaneously.

====================================================================
 WHAT ACTUALLY HELPS: LOWERING THEIR LUST
====================================================================
 The opponent's block is 100% ONLY while their Lust = 0%.
 As their Lust rises:
   - At Lust=50%: block chance drops to 50%
   - At Lust=80%: block chance = 20%
   - At Lust=100% (Mindless): no block, ALL your attacks hit Body directly

 If opponent goes Mindless:
   - Their effective kill target = 500 Body only (not 1000 total)
   - At 50% Lust, roughly half your attacks bypass their Mind
   - Kill time effectively 50-100% shorter

 LUST SPELL INTERACTION WHILE OPPONENT BLOCKS:
   "50% chance to suppress mental changes" while they are blocking.
   So lust effects from YOUR spells land 50% of the time even at full Mind.
   Each lust spell has a 50% chance to raise their Lust.
   Once raised, their block drops toward 0%.

 YOUR SPELLS VS THEIR RES=18:
   Pen=10 (base) vs Res=18: spell damage = 120 * 0.2 = 24 (negligible damage)
   BUT: lust STATUS EFFECT from the spell may still apply at 50% chance.
   => Use lust spells for Lust buildup, NOT for damage.

====================================================================
 REVISED STRATEGY: LUST + ATTACK HYBRID
====================================================================
 The correct approach vs this opponent:
   Phase A - Lust buildup: cast lust spells to push their Lust toward 50-100%
     Each spell may add lust at 50% success rate while they are blocking.
     At Lust=50%: their block = 50%, half their Mind mitigation gone.
     At Lust=100% (Mindless): kill target drops from 1000 to 500.

   Phase B - Kill window: once Mindless, spam attacks.
     All your attacks now hit Body directly.
     At x1.8 mult, 90 damage each: 500/90 = 6 attacks = ~60 seconds.
     Their spells still fire (they lose block, not spell ability).

 GEAR FOR THIS STRATEGY:
   Option A — Stay on Striker build (4Str+4Dex 4Hit+4Action)
   but treat early spells as Lust tools, not damage tools.
   You have MaxSpells=3.33 (base). Use first 3 naturally.
   Target: push their Lust quickly with all 3 at fight start.
   After that, pure attack spam while waiting for them to regen Lust.

   Option B — Add Spell secondary enchants (sacrifice some Action):
   4Str + 4Dex, 3Hit + 3Action + 2Spell (+0.68 MaxSpells)
   MaxSpells = 3.33 + 0.68 = 4.0  (1 extra lust spell available)
   MaxActions = 14/3 + 3*0.34 = 4.67+1.02 = 5.69
   Slightly slower attacks, slightly more lust pressure.

