====================================================================
 HONEST WIN CONDITION SUMMARY
====================================================================
 Against Pen=24 with no Resistance build on your side:
   - Kill target = 1000 (500 Mind + 500 Body)
   - Kill time for best offensive build = ~110 seconds
   - Incoming damage over 110s = more than your Mind+Body can absorb
   - Result: you die before killing them

 Against Pen=24 with Res=16 (Survivor):
   - Survive the 4-spell burst (barely, Body=181 after)
   - Kill time increases to 160s (they regen 2 spells during this)
   - Those 2 regen spells + post-burst attacks kill you at t=112
   - Result: still die 48 seconds short

 THE REAL COUNTER:
   Raise opponent Lust to 100% (Mindless) via lust spells in Phase A.
   Once Mindless, kill target = 500, achievable in ~55-80s.
   During lust buildup phase, they are still a threat.
   Surviving phase A is the key challenge.

   Best survival during Phase A = Survivor build (most total HP).
   Best Phase B kill speed = Striker build (highest DPS).
   Hybrid recommendation: Survivor stats + use all early spells for Lust.

====================================================================
 FIRST-TO-ZERO-BODY WINS — KEY RULES
====================================================================
 1. Damage routes (all, attacks and spells): Mind first, then Body.
 2. Block (100-Lust%) applies to all incoming damage including attacks.
 3. Mindless at Mind=0 or Lust=100%. Then everything hits Body.
 4. To kill someone: deal their MaxMind + MaxBody total damage.
 5. Opponent MaxMind = 500, MaxBody = 500 = 1000 kill target.
 6. Lust spells vs blocking opponent: 50% chance to apply per cast.
 7. Raising their Lust is the single most effective strategy:
    cuts their effective kill target from 1000 to 500 at Lust=100%.
